00:00:09.980 --> 00:00:13.740 align:middle line:84%
>> And when they do talk about
nutrition in medical school,

00:00:13.740 --> 00:00:16.790 align:middle line:84%
it's basically the
five food groups.

00:00:16.790 --> 00:00:20.310 align:middle line:90%
Maybe a multi vitamin every day.

00:00:20.310 --> 00:00:25.350 align:middle line:84%
Possibly a B12 injection
for people that are elderly.

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:29.490 align:middle line:84%
Maybe for pregnant women, we'd
better increase the folic acid

00:00:29.490 --> 00:00:30.390 align:middle line:90%
a little bit.

00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:33.630 align:middle line:84%
We should fortify foods with
small amounts of nutrients.

00:00:33.630 --> 00:00:35.210 align:middle line:84%
Since we took all
the nutrients out,

00:00:35.210 --> 00:00:36.840 align:middle line:84%
we should put a
few of them back.

00:00:36.840 --> 00:00:38.430 align:middle line:84%
That's like being
held up and having

00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:42.740 align:middle line:84%
somebody take $1,000 from you
and giving you a 5 in change.

00:00:42.740 --> 00:00:45.450 align:middle line:84%
It's a very strange
world that we have

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:49.650 align:middle line:84%
when nutrition is the last
thing we look at for therapy.

00:00:49.650 --> 00:00:52.560 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Roger J. Williams
who actually discovered

00:00:52.560 --> 00:00:57.180 align:middle line:84%
the vitamin pantothenic acid
and was Professor of Chemistry,

00:00:57.180 --> 00:00:59.980 align:middle line:90%
very, very brilliant man.

00:00:59.980 --> 00:01:04.650 align:middle line:84%
